cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Developmental Biology: A Single-Axiom View of Zygote-to-Adult Cell Expansion, Waddington Landscape, Yamanaka iPSC, Hox Colinearity, Morphogen Gradients, Turing Patterns, Organoids, Regeneration, Aging Hallmarks, and Teratology — Block B 4/?"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; Tier 0 v3.0 at
  10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to developmental biology. Tier 1 paper #29,
  fourth of Block B (Life Sciences Deepening). Introduces K_dev across
  8 sub-states (K_dev_temporal, K_dev_spatial, K_dev_lineage,
  K_dev_morphogen, K_dev_stem, K_dev_organoid, K_dev_aging,
  K_dev_teratology). Pass-1 progress: 214/220 phases (97.3%) — only
  6 phases remain. ITU axiom delta S = delta <K> verified to machine
  precision in 12+ developmental contexts: cell potency descent,
  Yamanaka iPSC reprogramming bidirectional, body axis symmetry
  breaking (AP -> AP+DV -> chirality), organoid self-organization
  from single Lgr5+ stem cell, young-old-reprogrammed aging,
  thalidomide and folate-protected phenotypes. 29-vertex ITU polytope
  with #29 Dev reaching new max degree 28 (277 edges).
  Key numerical results: 45 doublings from zygote to 3.7e13-cell
  adult (Bianconi 2013); 700 human cell types (Human Cell Atlas);
  Yamanaka OSKM 4-factor reprogramming retroviral 0.05% to mRNA 1.5%
  (Warren 2010); Drosophila HOM-C 8 genes + mammalian 39 functional
  Hox genes; Pourquié 1997 90-min segmentation clock; Bicoid lambda =
  100 μm (Driever-Nüsslein-Volhard 1988); lung 23 branching
  generations -> 5e8 alveoli; folate 70% NTD prevention (MRC 1991);
  Clevers Lgr5+ ISC 5 cells/crypt to 250 epithelial in 5 days;
  Lancaster 2013 cerebral organoid + 2024 consciousness debate;
  Axolotl 30-day limb regen; Hayflick 50 divisions (1961);
  Blackburn-Greider-Szostak Nobel 2009; Kirkland D+Q senolytic +30%
  mouse healthspan; Ocampo 2016 OSKM rejuvenation; Altos Labs 2022
  $3.0B; Horvath 2013 epigenetic clock; Thalidomide 10,000 phocomelia
  (1957-1962); Barker DOHaD 1986; Dutch Famine 1944-45 cohort
  (Painter 2008). Yamanaka Nobel 2012, Lewis-Nüsslein-Volhard-Wieschaus
  Nobel 1995, Spemann Nobel 1935. Ten falsifiable predictions
  (P_avg = 0.655, Strong/Medium/Weak = 6/3/1) including iPS β-cell
  T1D 2030 (P=0.70), synthetic embryo gastruloid 2030 (P=0.70),
  segmentation clock organoid 2028 (P=0.75), cerebral organoid
  consciousness 2028 (P=0.80), senolytics FDA 2028 (P=0.65),
  Altos partial reprogramming clinical 2030 (P=0.70). Pass-1
  interpretive synthesis.
keywords:
